&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you ready to step into a role where your skills meet purpose-and every day brings new ways to impact lives?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;At Claris Health, we’re searching for a passionate and adaptable Mid-Level Medical Provider to join our care team. Whether in one of our clinics or on our mobile medical unit, your ability to meet people where they are - clinically and emotionally - can transform the way someone experiences healthcare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn’t a role for someone looking for routine. We’re looking for a provider who thrives on flexibility, values patient dignity, and brings strong OB/GYN experience or the desire to grow in this field. If that sounds like you, we’d love to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;As a Mid-Level Medical Provider, you&#39;ll be an integral part of our patient care model, providing OB/GYN services across clinic sites and our mobile unit. You’ll conduct well-woman exams, prenatal care, STI testing and treatment, and patient education. You’ll also collaborate with our Clinic Director, supervise medical volunteers, and support medical assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires adaptability, empathy, and a deep commitment to caring for underserved populations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct pregnancy tests, female health screenings, and STI testing and treatment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide early prenatal care and lead Centering groups (if certified)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate patients on contraception, pregnancy loss, healthy pregnancy, and nutrition&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform and/or learn limited obstetric ultrasound&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rotate across clinics and mobile units, with occasional weekend outreach events&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Makes You a Great Fit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Licensed as a Physician Assistant, Nurse Practitioner, or Nurse Midwife in California&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum two years of OB/GYN experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OB Ultrasound training is preferred but not required. Will train the right candidate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working in mobile or community-based care settings is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable traveling across sites and stepping in wherever there’s a need&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Committed to excellen

